                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;09/22/2003&nbsp;: 06:42:27 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Well, I had my first go at LDON earlier tonight, and from reading some of the responses here earlier, I didn't have very good expectations of what the group would turn out to be like.<br /><br />I got a group started out of people I could find with their LFG tags up.  Initially I found 5 - Me (53 Necro), 55 Rogue, 54 Wiz, 5? Bst and a 5? Druid.  We sat around a little while then added a 56 Chanter to the group.<br /><br />Seeings I had formed the group, I told the people that joined earlier that I had never done LDON before and someone who had should be the leader.  We ported to BB, and on arrival, the Wizzie and I, both of us doing an LDON thing for the first time asked in group chat where abouts the adventurers camp was.<br /><br />Well, the chanter freaked out - "You have got to be kidding" or something like that and immdiately quit - then the rogue and beast quit too right away - not goodbyes, no sorries just gone.<br /><br />I was kind of pissed but still determined to have a go - so the wizzie and I went to the camp (Druid went LD but I thought she had quit too).  Stupid thing was, the 3 that had quit were there LFG but they didn't want to have a bar of our newbie group.<br /><br />Druid came back, brought along a 55 Cleric and then all of a sudden the rogue wants back in.  I really didn't want to let him join and told him so, but the others were keen to get going so he was back in.  We then got a 56 warrior and were set.<br /><br />It was my first time in a group since my 30's so I was kind of nervous to be doing crowd control, but thanks to the cleric being on the ball when I would get mega aggro from mezzing a mob, things turned out great.<br /><br />We only did a normal difficulty setting as at least 2 of us were first timers, but I was really happy at how well I could control the adds, and slowing the undead made me really poplular too.<br /><br />Was fun and proved to the others there that you don't need a chanter (specially stuck up ones like the dick that joined us) to pull of these small dungeon crawls.<br /><br /></span></font></td>
